body:
Commission Update!

With the influx of new art I have decided to update my references and make a new post! So the prices correspond to the pictures above from upper left to bottom right.

Sketch:

  • Bust: $5
  • Half body: $15
  • Full body: $25

Lineart:

  • Bust: $10
  • Half body: $20
  • Full body: $30

Flat Color:

Full Illustration:

  • Bust: $20 - $40
  • Half body: $40 - $60

I reserve the right to refuse any commissions that I am not comfortable with but feel free to ask about anything ahead of time and provide lots of reference.

summary:
Howdy guys! I made a closed species thingy again XD
I call em Downy Dogs! However, they also can be called Droop Snoots cause i...
body:
Howdy guys! I made a closed species thingy again XD

I call em Downy Dogs! However, they also can be called Droop Snoots cause i liked both options and that’s basically what they are oof.

Downy dogs are creatures that are passive aggressive, live in packs, and have snouts that are normally in a downward facing position.

Build and Behavior info:

Their snouts (aka their drooped snoots *wink wonk*) may be facing downward, however their jaws can stretch extremely wide open in what would look unnatural considering their bone structure. They can switch between bipedal (two legs) and all fours with ease, and tend to be very large in height on their hind legs, ranging from 6-9 feet in height normally along with Alpha-born dogs being at about 8-10 feet tall when bipedal. Their horns can eventually wear down to curved nubs or grow into large antler-like horns, as to which female horns will always have a tip curved forward while males have the tip horns curved backward. And yes, they all have 4 ears, which can be pointed, floppy, or both simultaneously.

Their fur colors vary, but all of them have distinctive multicolored patterns along their backs. They tend to have extra long fur on the backs of their hind legs, and their front paws are slightly different than their hind paws considering the front paws are more hand-like in bone structure.

So they’re supposed to be protective, yet still friendly creatures so an encounter with one would make it seem like how you would behave if you were acquaintances already. Despite their friendly nature, they’re still alert, and won’t hesitate to become aggressive if they sense a possible threat.

I’m still working on more info but I hope y’all like what I got so far! ^w^ I’m not sure if I’ll open them as a public species later on or at least a regulated one like Dutch Angel Dragons are since I guess they’re basically furries i guess oof. Feel free to ask questions about Downy Dogs, I’ll try my best to answer them! Feel free to let me know what u think of em too! :3
